:'''Howard:''' Hahaha, I really should correct this bad habit of talking to myself.
:'''Howard:''' I've grown infatuated recently with the mysteries of Xianzhou culture. I've been obsessed with thinking about them...
:'''Howard:''' In one of them, there are drakons in the Lunarescent Depths that can live for thousands of years &mdash; and their tears crystallize into pearls. It's enough to set the mind racing!
:'''Howard:''' But the Scalegorge Waterscape delves generally don't let Outworlders like us go down, and the Draconic Tears out on the market are all too processed, so they lack that legendary authenticity.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} You sure are fussy.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_412221207-->
::'''Howard:''' These are pharmaceuticals, but on the open market they always end up looking like sparkly jewels &mdash; all scrubbed up nice and pretty to pander to those hunting for legends. Or perhaps that's going a bit too far.
::'''Howard:''' Me, I may be an Outworlder but I like local customs and use whatever the locals use. Super-clean and clear Draconic Tears are too fake for me, and aren't worth collecting.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I've got some all-natural ones right here.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_412221210-->
:::'''Howard:''' I just like natural, unclean Draconic Tears. Let me have a look.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Same.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_412221212-->
:::'''Howard:''' Looks like we've something in common. Birds of a feather flock together, haha!
:::'''Howard:''' Seeing as we're so similar then, have you got any Draconic Tears for me?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Actually, I've got some Draconic Tears right here.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_412221215-->
::'''Howard:''' I've seen too many Draconic Tears on the markets, so I hope you can show me something a little different.
:<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_412221216-->
