;(First interaction)
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 90000057: Config/Level/NPC/W2/NPC_DefaultStory_502011201.json-->
::'''Howard:''' "I'd rather have three days without food than go one day without tea." I mean, the Xianzhou natives have to drink tea even if they're starving. I've drunk my fill of tea, too &mdash; and zero calories, too. It's a pretty interesting turn of phrase.
::'''Howard:''' Vegetations in the Alchemy Cauldron, Whale-Tide Spring, Emerald Hills, and Hunter Maofeng...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} If you ask me, Whale-Tide Spring's the best.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502112004-->
:::'''Howard:''' Whale-Tide Spring? Hold on, let me look up some good quotes about tea.
:::'''Howard:''' "Whale-Tide Spring buds are tender. Bake-drying results in knotted strips as fine hairs appear with a silvery green hue. Brew to create swirling clouds in your teacup. Its mild fragrance is striking..."
:::'''Howard:''' It's all in unintelligible Xianzhou words. But that's okay, no harm in ordering a pot of Whale-Tide Spring tea.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Actually, I don't really know much about tea.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502112008-->
:::'''Howard:''' Hahaha, I can tell! You're an Outworlder with a curiosity for Xianzhou culture.
:::'''Howard:''' Ordering tea aboard Xianzhou isn't the easiest thing, and you might not get all the cultural allusions going on. But that's just my own bad habit, {{MC|f=m'girl|m=boy}} &mdash; you don't have to be like me.
:::'''Howard:''' This Whale-Tide Spring is awesome, and I'll sit on a pot of this for a while.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} May as well just close my eyes and pick out one at random, right?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502112012-->
:::'''Howard:''' {{MC|f=Girl|m=Boy}}, you're an Outworlder just like me. You're not exactly wrong, but it's really quite rude.
:::'''Howard:''' Xianzhou tea drinking is steeped in history, culture, decorum, and rules. If one were to glug it down like some common ruffian, it would sully the tea's heritage...
:::'''Howard:''' This Whale-Tide Spring is awesome, and I'll sit on a pot of this for a while.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502112015-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502112015-->
::'''Howard:''' The name's Howard. I'm a trade commissioner for the Interastral Peace Corporation, or IPC. I've come here to trade tech with Xianzhou. A pleasure to make your acquaintance.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} It's a pleasure to meet you, I'm (Trailblazer).
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'm (Trailblazer).
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502112025-->
::'''Howard:''' Hahaha, fate has brought us together. Take this small gift. "Small gifts in place of vast appreciation," as they say. Please accept it.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502011201_29-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502011201_29-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You must be quite a fan of the Xianzhou culture.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502112019-->
:::'''Howard:''' Hahaha, I already knew a little about Xianzhou culture back at HQ. Now I have the opportunity to be stationed here, I have prepared ahead.
:::'''Howard:''' The more I studied it, the more fascinated I became... despite everyone at work jokingly calling me "Mr. Xianzhou," my knowledge about Xianzhou culture really is just a drop in the bucket.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I think you already know far more than I do.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502112022-->
:::'''Howard:''' You're too kind. I know this is the famous "humility," right? "The dragonfruit never sings about its sweetness."
:::'''Howard:''' It feels like there are secret masters hidden throughout Xianzhou, each pretending to be super-normal. What a fascinating phenomenon.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502112024-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502112024-->
::'''Howard:''' I've had a great time chatting with you, {{MC|f=m'girl|m=boy}}. If there's anything you'd like to know, I'll definitely tell you everything. Consider me your new friend.
;(Subsequent interactions)
